<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658830>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 3. Boreoacanthomysis schrencki (Czerniavsky, 1882) comb. nov.: NSMT-Cr 15111. (A– E, H–J) Male (9.1 mm); (F, G) male (9.5 mm); (K) female (13.3 mm). (A–C) First to third pleopod, anterior surface; (D) fourth pleopod, posterior surface (seta at outer distal angle of proximal segment broken); (E) fifth pleopod, anterior surface; (F) fourth pleopod, posterior surface; (G) fifth pleopod, anterior surface; (H) basal part of endopod of uropod, ventral; (I) telson and uropod of male, dorsal; (J) distal part of telson, dorsal; (K) telson and uropod of female, dorsal." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4658830/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658826>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 1. Boreoacanthomysis schrencki (Czerniavsky, 1882) comb. nov.: NSMT-Cr 15111. (A, C, E–G) Male (9.1 mm); (B, D, H) female (13.3 mm). (A, B) Anterior end of body, dorsal; (C) antennal scale of male, dorsal; (D) antennal scale of female, ventral; (E) labrum, lateral; (F) mandible; (G, H) maxillule, posterior surface." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4658826/files/figure.png" .

